{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_27763f7d3ffeGH5F5fsk7eU9xK","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d889c1fe8001Xm9ZVlElmzRyGV","parts":[{"id":"prt_d889c2c1a0012Zdf43XjwXEcdb","messageID":"msg_d889c1fe8001Xm9ZVlElmzRyGV","sessionID":"ses_27763f7d3ffeGH5F5fsk7eU9xK","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_2312bf46a94d45839117ec82","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/setup.sh"},"output":"<path>/workspace/setup.sh</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: #!/usr/bin/env bash\n2: \n3: setup_columnflow() {\n4:     # Runs the entire project setup, leading to a collection of environment variables starting with\n5:     # \"CF_\", the installation of the software stack via virtual environments, and optionally an\n6:     # interactive setup where the user can configure certain variables.\n7:     #\n8:     # Arguments:\n9:     #   1. The name of the setup. \"default\" (which is itself the default when no name is set)\n10:     #      triggers a setup with good defaults, avoiding all queries to the user and the writing of\n11:     #      a custom setup file. See \"interactive_setup()\" for more info.\n12:     #\n13:     # Boolean flags are considered true-ish if they are \"1\", \"yes\" or \"true\" (case-insensitive).\n14:     #\n15:     # Optionally preconfigured environment variables:\n16:     #   CF_REINSTALL_SOFTWARE\n17:     #       When true-ish, any existing software stack is removed and freshly installed.\n18:     #   CF_REINSTALL_HOOKS\n19:     #       When true-ish, existing git hooks are removed and linked again.\n20:     #   CF_REMOTE_ENV\n21:     #       When true-ish, applies configurations for remote job. Remote jobs will set this value if needed\n22:     #       and there is no need to set this by hand.\n23:     #   CF_LCG_SETUP\n24:     #       The location of a custom LCG software setup file.\n25:     #   X509_USER_PROXY\n26:     #       A custom globus user proxy location.\n27:     #   LANGUAGE, LANG, LC_ALL\n28:     #       Custom language flags.\n29:     #\n30:     # Variables defined by the setup and potentially required throughout columnflow:\n31:     #   CF_SETUP_NAME\n32:     #       The name of the setup. See above.\n33:     #   CF_BASE\n34:     #       The absolute columnflow base directory. Used to infer file locations relative to it.\n35:     #   CF_DATA\n36:     #       The main data directory where outputs and software can be stored in. Internally, this\n37:     #       serves as a default for e.g. $CF_SOFTWARE_BASE, $CF_CMSSW_BASE, $CF_JOB_BASE and\n38:     #       $CF_VENV_BASE which can, however, potentially point to a different directory. Queried\n39:     #       during the interactive setup.\n40:     #   CF_PYTHON_VERSION\n41:     #       The python version to use for the conda and venv installations. Defaults to \"3.9\".\n42:     #   CF_SOFTWARE_BASE\n43:     #       The directory where general software is installed. Might point to $CF_DATA/software.\n44:     #       Queried during the interactive setup.\n45:     #   CF_REPO_BASE\n46:     #       The base path of the main repository invoking tasks or scripts. Used by columnflow tasks\n47:     #       to identify the repository that is bundled into remote jobs. Set to $CF_BASE when not\n48:     #       defined already.\n49:     #   CF_REPO_BASE_ALIAS\n50:     #       Name of an environment variable whose value is identical to that of CF_REPO_BASE and\n51:     #      that is usually used by an upstream analysis. For instance, if the analysis base is\n52:     #      stored in \"$MY_ANALYSIS_BASE\", CF_REPO_BASE_ALIAS should be \"MY_ANALYSIS_BASE\" (no $).\n53:     #   CF_CONDA_BASE\n54:     #       The directory where conda / micromamba and conda envs are installed. Might point to\n55:     #       $CF_SOFTWARE_BASE/conda.\n56:     #   CF_VENV_BASE\n57:     #       The directory where virtual envs are installed. Might point to $CF_SOFTWARE_BASE/venvs.\n58:     #   CF_CMSSW_BASE\n59:     #       The directory where CMSSW releases are installed. Might point to\n60:     #       $CF_SOFTWARE_BASE/cmssw.\n61:     #   CF_JOB_BASE\n62:     #       The directory where job files from batch system submissions are kept. Used in law.cfg.\n63:     #       Might point to $CF_DATA/jobs. Queried during the interactive setup.\n64:     #   CF_VENV_SETUP_MODE\n65:     #       The default mode for setting up virtual envs. Queried during the interactive setup. See\n66:     #       sandboxes/_setup_venv.sh for more info.\n67:     #   CF_STORE_NAME\n68:     #       The name (not path) of store directories that will be created to contain output targets,\n69:     #       potentially both locally and remotely. Queried during the interactive setup.\n70:     #   CF_STORE_LOCAL\n71:     #       The default local output store path, ammended by $CF_STORE_NAME. Queried during the\n72:     #       interactive setup.\n73:     #   CF_CI_ENV\n74:     #       Set to \"true\" if a CI environment is detected (e.g. GitHub actions), and \"false\"\n75:     #       otherwise.\n76:     #   CF_RTD_ENV\n77:     #       Set to \"true\" if a READTHEDOCS environment is detected, and \"false\" otherwise.\n78:     #   CF_LCG_SETUP\n79:     #       The location of a custom LCG software setup file. See above.\n80:     #   CF_PERSISTENT_PATH\n81:     #       PATH fragments that should be considered by sandboxes (bash, venv, cmssw) to have\n82:     #       precedence, e.g. to ensure that executables of local packages are priotized.\n83:     #   CF_PERSISTENT_PYTHONPATH\n84:     #       PYTHONPATH fragments that should be considered by sandboxes (bash, venv, cmssw) to have\n85:     #       precedence, e.g. to ensure that python modules of local packages are priotized.\n86:     #   CF_CONDA_PYTHONPATH\n87:     #       PYTHONPATH fragments pointing to packages intalled by conda.\n88:     #   CF_ORIG_PATH\n89:     #       Copy of the $PATH variable before ammended by the setup.\n90:     #   CF_ORIG_PYTHONPATH\n91:     #       Copy of the $PYTHONPATH variable before ammended by the setup.\n92:     #   CF_ORIG_PYTHON3PATH\n93:     #       Copy of the $PYTHON3PATH variable before ammended by the setup.\n94:     #   CF_ORIG_LD_LIBRARY_PATH\n95:     #       Copy of the $LD_LIBRARY_PATH variable before ammended by the setup.\n96:     #   CF_WLCG_CACHE_ROOT\n97:     #       The directory in which remote files from WLCG locations might be cached. No caching is\n98:     #       used when empty. Queried during the interactive setup. Used in law.cfg.\n99:     #   CF_WLCG_USE_CACHE\n100:     #       Saves the decision on whether WLCG file caching is used or not, based on\n101:     #       $CF_WLCG_CACHE_ROOT. Set to \"true\" when a remote job environment is detected. Used in\n102:     #       law.cfg.\n103:     #   CF_WLCG_CACHE_CLEANUP\n104:     #       Set to \"false\" when the variable is not already existing. When \"false\", caches are not\n105:     #       cleared after programs terminate and become persistent. Set to \"true\" when a remove job\n106:     #       environment is detected. Used in law.cfg.\n107:     #   CF_CERN_USER\n108:     #       The user's CERN / WLCG name. Used in law.cfg.\n109:     #   CF_CERN_USER_FIRSTCHAR\n110:     #       The first character of the user's CERN / WLCG name. Derived from $CF_CERN_USER. Used in\n111:     #       law.cfg.\n112:     #   CF_LOCAL_SCHEDULER\n113:     #       Either \"true\" or \"false\", deciding whether the process-local luigi scheduler should be\n114:     #       used by default. Queried during the interactive setup. Used in law.cfg.\n115:     #   CF_SCHEDULER_HOST\n116:     #       Set to \"127.0.0.1\" when $CF_LOCAL_SCHEDULER was set to \"true\", or otherwise queried\n117:     #       during the interactive setup. Used in law.cfg.\n118:     #   CF_SCHEDULER_PORT\n119:     #       Set to \"8082\" when $CF_LOCAL_SCHEDULER was set to \"true\", or otherwise queried during\n120:     #       the interactive setup. Used in law.cfg.\n121:     #   CF_WORKER_KEEP_ALIVE\n122:     #       Set to \"false\" when not already set, or when a remote ($CF_REMOTE_ENV) or CI environment\n123:     #       ($CF_CI_ENV) is detected. Used in law.cfg.\n124:     #   CF_HTCONDOR_FLAVOR\n125:     #       The default htcondor flavor setting for the HTCondorWorkflow task.\n126:     #   CF_SLURM_FLAVOR\n127:     #       The default slurm flavor setting for the SlurmWorkflow task.\n128:     #   CF_SLURM_PARTITION\n129:     #       The default slurm partition setting for the SlurmWorkflow task.\n130:     #   CF_CRAB_STORAGE_ELEMENT\n131:     #       The storage element for storing crab job related outputs.\n132:     #   CF_CRAB_BASE_DIRECTORY\n133:     #       The base directory where to store crab job related outputs on CF_CRAB_STORAGE_ELEMENT.\n134:     #   CF_SETUP\n135:     #       A flag that is set to 1 after the setup was successful.\n136:     #   PATH\n137:     #       Ammended PATH variable.\n138:     #   PYTHONPATH\n139:     #       Ammended PYTHONPATH variable.\n140:     #   PYTHONWARNINGS\n141:     #       Set to \"ignore\" when not defined already.\n142:     #   PYTHONNOUSERSITE\n143:     #       Set to \"1\" when not defined alreedy, to prevent python from loading packages from e.g.\n144:     #       \"$HOME/.local\", which can lead to encapsulation and debugging issues.\n145:     #   GLOBUS_THREAD_MODEL\n146:     #       Set to \"none\".\n147:     #   MYPROXY_SERVER\n148:     #       Set to \"myproxy.cern.ch\".\n149:     #   VIRTUAL_ENV_DISABLE_PROMPT\n150:     #       Set to \"true\" when not defined already, leading to virtual envs leaving the PS1 prompt\n151:     #       variable unaltered.\n152:     #   X509_USER_PROXY\n153:     #       Set to \"/tmp/x509up_u$( id -u )\" if not already set.\n154:     #   LAW_HOME\n155:     #       Set to \"$CF_BASE/.law\" if not already set.\n156:     #   LAW_CONFIG_FILE\n157:     #       Set to \"$CF_BASE/law.cfg\" if not already set.\n158: \n159:     # prevent repeated setups\n160:     if ${CF_SETUP}; then\n161:         >&2 echo \"columnflow was already succesfully setup\"\n162:         >&2 echo \"re-running the setup requires a new shell\"\n163:         return \"1\"\n164:     fi\n165: \n166:     #\n167:     # prepare local variables\n168:     #\n169: \n170:     local shell_is_zsh=\"$( [ -z \"${ZSH_VERSION}\" ] && echo \"false\" || echo \"true\" )\"\n171:     local this_file=\"$( ${shell_is_zsh} && echo \"${(%):-%x}\" || echo \"${BASH_SOURCE[0]}\" )\"\n172:     local this_dir=\"$( cd \"$( dirname \"${this_file}\" )\" && pwd )\"\n173:     local orig=\"${PWD}\"\n174:     local setup_name=\"${1:-default}\"\n175:     local setup_is_default=\"false\"\n176:     [ \"${setup_name}\" = \"default\" ] && setup_is_default=\"true\"\n177: \n178:     # zsh options\n179:     if ${shell_is_zsh}; then\n180:         emulate -L bash\n181:         setopt globdots\n182:     fi\n183: \n184:     #\n185:     # global variables\n186:     # (CF = columnflow)\n187:     #\n188: \n189:     # start exporting variables\n190:     export CF_BASE=\"${this_dir}\"\n191:     export CF_SETUP_NAME=\"${setup_name}\"\n192: \n193:     # interactive setup\n194:     if ! ${CF_REMOTE_ENV}; then\n195:         cf_setup_interactive_body() {\n196:             # query common variables\n197:             cf_setup_interactive_common_variables\n198:         }\n199:         cf_setup_interactive \"${CF_SETUP_NAME}\" \"${CF_BASE}/.setups/${CF_SETUP_NAME}.sh\" || return \"$?\"\n200:     fi\n201: \n202:     # continue the fixed setup\n203:     export CF_REPO_BASE=\"${CF_REPO_BASE:-$CF_BASE}\"\n204:     export CF_REPO_BASE_ALIAS=\"${CF_REPO_BASE_ALIAS:-}\"\n205:     export CF_CONDA_BASE=\"${CF_CONDA_BASE:-${CF_SOFTWARE_BASE}/conda}\"\n206:     export CF_VENV_BASE=\"${CF_VENV_BASE:-${CF_SOFTWARE_BASE}/venvs}\"\n207:     export CF_CMSSW_BASE=\"${CF_CMSSW_BASE:-${CF_SOFTWARE_BASE}/cmssw}\"\n208:     export CF_ORIG_PATH=\"${PATH}\"\n209:     export CF_ORIG_PYTHONPATH=\"${PYTHONPATH}\"\n210:     export CF_ORIG_PYTHON3PATH=\"${PYTHON3PATH}\"\n211:     export CF_ORIG_LD_LIBRARY_PATH=\"${LD_LIBRARY_PATH}\"\n212: \n213:     #\n214:     # common variables\n215:     #\n216: \n217:     cf_setup_common_variables || return \"$?\"\n218: \n219:     #\n220:     # minimal local software setup\n221:     #\n222: \n223:     cf_setup_software_stack \"${CF_SETUP_NAME}\" || return \"$?\"\n224: \n225:     #\n226:     # additional common cf setup steps\n227:     #\n228: \n229:     cf_setup_post_install || return \"$?\"\n230: \n231:     #\n232:     # finalize\n233:     #\n234: \n235:     export CF_SETUP=\"true\"\n236: }\n237: \n238: cf_detect_envs() {\n239:     # Uses specific environment variables to detect if the current environment is a special one, e.g. in a remote job,\n240:     # in a CI job, or in a READTHEDOCS build.\n241: \n242:     # detect variables (not using cf_cast_bool since services might use different values)\n243:     export CF_CI_ENV=\"$( [ \"$( cf_lower_case \"${GITHUB_ACTIONS}\" )\" = \"true\" ] && echo \"true\" || echo \"false\" )\"\n244:     export CF_RTD_ENV=\"$( [ \"$( cf_lower_case \"${READTHEDOCS}\" )\" = \"true\" ] && echo \"true\" || echo \"false\" )\"\n245: \n246:     # store env flags\n247:     export CF_LOCAL_ENV=\"false\"\n248:     if ${CF_REMOTE_ENV}; then\n249:         cf_color yellow \"detected remote job environment\"\n250:     elif ${CF_CI_ENV}; then\n251:         cf_color yellow \"detected CI environment\"\n252:     elif ${CF_RTD_ENV}; then\n253:         cf_color yellow \"detected READTHEDOCS environment\"\n254:     else\n255:         export CF_LOCAL_ENV=\"true\"\n256:     fi\n257: }\n258: [ ! -z \"${BASH_VERSION}\" ] && export -f cf_detect_envs\n259: \n260: cf_setup_common_variables() {\n261:     # Exports variables that might be commonly used across analyses, such as host and job\n262:     # environment variables (or their defaults).\n263: \n264:     # detect environments\n265:     cf_detect_envs || return \"$?\"\n266: \n267:     # lang defaults\n268:     if ${CF_RTD_ENV}; then\n269:         export LANGUAGE=\"${READTHEDOCS_LANGUAGE:-en}\"\n270:         export LANG=\"${READTHEDOCS_LANGUAGE:-en}\"\n271:         export LC_ALL=\"${READTHEDOCS_LANGUAGE:-en}\"\n272:     elif ${CF_ON_GRID}; then\n273:         : # not supported on grid\n274:     else\n275:         export LANGUAGE=\"${LANGUAGE:-en_US.UTF-8}\"\n276:         export LANG=\"${LANG:-en_US.UTF-8}\"\n277:         export LC_ALL=\"${LC_ALL:-en_US.UTF-8}\"\n278:     fi\n279: \n280:     # proxy\n281:     export X509_USER_PROXY=\"${X509_USER_PROXY:-/tmp/x509up_u$( id -u )}\"\n282: \n283:     # overwrite some variables in remote and ci jobs\n284:     if ${CF_REMOTE_ENV}; then\n285:         export CF_WLCG_USE_CACHE=\"true\"\n286:         export CF_WLCG_CACHE_CLEANUP=\"true\"\n287:         export CF_WORKER_KEEP_ALIVE=\"false\"\n288:     elif ${CF_CI_ENV} || ${CF_RTD_ENV}; then\n289:         export CF_WLCG_USE_CACHE=\"false\"\n290:         export CF_WLCG_CACHE_CLEANUP=\"false\"\n291:         export CF_WORKER_KEEP_ALIVE=\"false\"\n292:     fi\n293: \n294:     # luigi worker and scheduler defaults (assigned in law.cfg)\n295:     export CF_WORKER_KEEP_ALIVE=\"${CF_WORKER_KEEP_ALIVE:-false}\"\n296:     export CF_SCHEDULER_HOST=\"${CF_SCHEDULER_HOST:-127.0.0.1}\"\n297:     export CF_SCHEDULER_PORT=\"${CF_SCHEDULER_PORT:-8082}\"\n298: \n299:     # default job flavor settings (starting with naf / maxwell cluster defaults)\n300:     # used by law.cfg and, in turn, tasks/framework/remote.py\n301:     local cf_htcondor_flavor_default=\"naf\"\n302:     local cf_slurm_flavor_default=\"maxwell\"\n303:     local cf_slurm_partition_default=\"maxgpu\"\n304:     local hname=\"$( hostname 2> /dev/null )\"\n305:     if [ \"$?\" = \"0\" ]; then\n306:         # lxplus\n307:         if [[ \"${hname}\" == lx*.cern.ch ]]; then\n308:             cf_htcondor_flavor_default=\"cern\"\n309:         fi\n310:     fi\n311:     export CF_HTCONDOR_FLAVOR=\"${CF_HTCONDOR_FLAVOR:-${cf_htcondor_flavor_default}}\"\n312:     export CF_SLURM_FLAVOR=\"${CF_SLURM_FLAVOR:-${cf_slurm_flavor_default}}\"\n313:     export CF_SLURM_PARTITION=\"${CF_SLURM_PARTITION:-${cf_slurm_partition_default}}\"\n314: \n315:     # show a warning in case no CF_REPO_BASE_ALIAS is set\n316:     if [ -z \"${CF_REPO_BASE_ALIAS}\" ]; then\n317:         cf_color yellow \"the variable CF_REPO_BASE_ALIAS is unset\"\n318:         cf_color yellow \"please consider setting it to the name of the variable that refers to your analysis base directory\"\n319:     fi\n320: \n321:     # notification variables\n322:     export CF_MATTERMOST_HOOK_URL=\"${CF_MATTERMOST_HOOK_URL:-}\"\n323:     export CF_MATTERMOST_CHANNEL=\"${CF_MATTERMOST_CHANNEL:-}\"\n324: }\n325: \n326: cf_show_banner() {\n327:     local no_utf8=\"$( cf_cast_bool \"${1}\" )\"\n328:     if ! ${no_utf8}; then\n329:         local charmap=\"$( cf_lower_case \"$( locale charmap )\" )\"\n330:         no_utf8=\"$( [ \"${charmap}\" = \"utf-8\" ] && echo \"false\" || echo \"true\" )\"\n331:     fi\n332: \n333:     if ${no_utf8}; then\n334:         cat << EOF\n335:                 $( cf_color green '_' )\n336:     ___   ___  $( cf_color green '| |' ) _   _  _ __ ___   _ __\n337:    / __| / _ \\ $( cf_color green '| |' )| | | || '_ \\` _ \\ | '_ \\\\\n338:   | (__ | (_) |$( cf_color green '| |' )| |_| || | | | | || | | |\n339:    \\___| \\___/ $( cf_color green '| |' ) \\__,_||_| |_| |_||_| |_|\n340:             __ $( cf_color green '| |' )\n341:            / _|$( cf_color green '| |' )  ___ __      __\n342:           | |_ $( cf_color green '| |' ) / _ \\\\ \\ /\\ / /\n343:           |  _|$( cf_color green '| |' )| (_) |\\ V  V /\n344:           |_|  $( cf_color green '| |' ) \\___/  \\_/\\_/\n345:                $( cf_color green '|_|' )\n346: \n347: EOF\n348:     else\n349:         cat << EOF\n350: \n351:   ┏┏┓$( cf_color green '┃' )╻┏┏┳┓┏┓\n352:   ┗┗┛$( cf_color green '┃' )┗┛╹┗┗╹┗\n353:     ┏$( cf_color green '┃' )\n354:     ╋$( cf_color green '┃' )┏┓┓┏┏\n355:     ┛$( cf_color green '┃' )┗┛┗┻┛\n356: \n357: EOF\n358:     fi\n359: }\n360: \n361: cf_setup_interactive_common_variables() {\n362:     # Queries for common variables which should be called from called inside custom\n363:     # cf_setup_interactive_body funtions, which in turn is called by cf_setup_interactive.\n364: \n365:     query CF_CERN_USER \"CERN username\" \"$( whoami )\"\n366:     export_and_save CF_CERN_USER_FIRSTCHAR \"\\${CF_CERN_USER:0:1}\"\n367: \n368:     query CF_DATA \"Local data directory\" \"\\$$( [ -z \"${CF_REPO_BASE}\" ] && echo \"CF_BASE\" || echo \"CF_REPO_BASE\" )/data\" \"./data\"\n369:     query CF_SOFTWARE_BASE \"Local directory for installing software\" \"\\$CF_DATA/software\"\n370:     query CF_JOB_BASE \"Local directory for storing job files\" \"\\$CF_DATA/jobs\"\n371: \n372:     query CF_STORE_NAME \"Relative path used in store paths (see next queries)\" \"cf_store\"\n373:     query CF_STORE_LOCAL \"Default local output store\" \"\\$CF_DATA/\\$CF_STORE_NAME\"\n374:     query CF_WLCG_CACHE_ROOT \"Local directory for caching remote files\" \"\" \"''\"\n375:     export_and_save CF_WLCG_USE_CACHE \"$( [ -z \"${CF_WLCG_CACHE_ROOT}\" ] && echo \"false\" || echo \"true\" )\"\n376:     export_and_save CF_WLCG_CACHE_CLEANUP \"${CF_WLCG_CACHE_CLEANUP:-false}\"\n377: \n378:     query CF_VENV_SETUP_MODE_UPDATE \"Automatically update virtual envs if needed\" \"false\"\n379:     [ \"${CF_VENV_SETUP_MODE_UPDATE}\" != \"true\" ] && export_and_save CF_VENV_SETUP_MODE \"update\"\n380:     unset CF_VENV_SETUP_MODE_UPDATE\n381:     query CF_INTERACTIVE_VENV_FILE \"Custom venv setup file to use for interactive work instead of 'cf_dev'\" \"\" \"''\"\n382: \n383:     query CF_LOCAL_SCHEDULER \"Use a local scheduler for law tasks\" \"true\"\n384:     if [ \"${CF_LOCAL_SCHEDULER}\" != \"true\" ]; then\n385:         query CF_SCHEDULER_HOST \"Address of a central scheduler for law tasks\" \"127.0.0.1\"\n386:         query CF_SCHEDULER_PORT \"Port of a central scheduler for law tasks\" \"8082\"\n387:     else\n388:         export_and_save CF_SCHEDULER_HOST \"127.0.0.1\"\n389:         export_and_save CF_SCHEDULER_PORT \"8082\"\n390:     fi\n391: \n392:     query CF_FLAVOR \"Flavor of the columnflow setup ('', 'cms')\" \"${CF_FLAVOR:-''}\"\n393: \n394:     if [ \"${CF_FLAVOR}\" = \"cms\" ]; then\n395:         query LAW_CMS_VO \"virtual orgranistion\" \"cms\"\n396:         query CF_CRAB_STORAGE_ELEMENT \"storage element for crab specific job outputs (e.g. T2_DE_DESY)\" \"''\"\n397:         query CF_CRAB_BASE_DIRECTORY \"base directory on storage element for crab specific job outputs\" \"/store/user/\\$CF_CERN_USER/cf_crab_outputs\"\n398:     fi\n399: }\n400: \n401: cf_setup_interactive() {\n402:     # Starts the interactive part of the setup by querying for values of certain environment\n403:     # variables with useful defaults. When a custom, named setup is triggered, the values of all\n404:     # queried environment variables are stored in a file.\n405:     #\n406:     # The actual variables that should be queried and exported during the setup are to be defined\n407:     # beforehand a function called \"cf_setup_interactive_body\". This function can make use of the\n408:     # internal functions \"export_and_save\" and \"query\", defined below.\n409:     #\n410:     # Arguments:\n411:     #   1. The name of the setup. \"default\" triggers a setup with good defaults, avoiding all\n412:     #      queries to the user and the writing of a custom setup file.\n413:     #   2. The location of the setup file when a custom, named setup was triggered.\n414:     #\n415:     # Optionally preconfigured environment variables:\n416:     #   CF_SKIP_BANNER\n417:     #       When true-ish, the \"columnflow\" banner is not shown.\n418: \n419:     local setup_name=\"${1}\"\n420:     local env_file=\"${2}\"\n421:     local env_file_tmp=\"${env_file}.tmp\"\n422:     local setup_is_default=\"false\"\n423:     [ \"${setup_name}\" = \"default\" ] && setup_is_default=\"true\"\n424: \n425:     # optionally show the banner\n426:     ${CF_SKIP_BANNER} || cf_show_banner\n427: \n428:     # when the setup already exists and it's not the default one,\n429:     # source the corresponding env file and stop\n430:     if ! ${setup_is_default}; then\n431:         if [ -f \"${env_file}\" ]; then\n432:             echo \"using variables for setup '$( cf_color magenta ${setup_name} )' from ${env_file}\"\n433:             source \"${env_file}\" \"\"\n434:             return \"$?\"\n435:         elif [ -z \"${env_file}\" ]; then\n436:             >&2 echo \"no env file passed as 2nd argument to cf_interactive_setup\"\n437:             return \"1\"\n438:         else\n439:             echo \"no setup file ${env_file} found for setup '$( cf_color magenta ${setup_name} )'\"\n440:         fi\n441:     fi\n442: \n443:     export_and_save() {\n444:         local varname=\"$1\"\n445:         local value=\"$2\"\n446: \n447:         export $varname=\"$( eval \"echo ${value}\" )\"\n448:         if ! ${setup_is_default}; then\n449:             echo \"export ${varname}=\\\"${value}\\\"\" >> \"${env_file_tmp}\"\n450:         fi\n451:     }\n452: \n453:     query() {\n454:         local varname=\"$1\"\n455:         local text=\"$2\"\n456:         local default=\"$3\"\n457:         local default_text=\"${4:-${default}}\"\n458:         local default_lower=\"$( cf_lower_case \"${default}\" )\"\n459: \n460:         # when the setup is the default one, use the default value when the env variable is empty,\n461:         # otherwise, query interactively\n462:         local value=\"${default}\"\n463:         if ${setup_is_default}; then\n464:             # set the variable when existing\n465:             eval \"value=\\${$varname:-\\${value}}\"\n466:         else\n467:             local query_response\n468:             local query_response_lower\n469: \n470:             printf \"${text} ($( cf_color default_bright ${varname} ), default $( cf_color default_bright ${default_text} )):  \"\n471:             read query_response\n472:             [ \"X${query_response}\" = \"X\" ] && query_response=\"${default}\"\n473: \n474:             # repeat for boolean flags that were not entered correctly\n475:             while true; do\n476:                 ( [ \"${default_lower}\" != \"true\" ] && [ \"${default_lower}\" != \"false\" ] ) && break\n477:                 query_response_lower=\"$( cf_lower_case \"${query_response}\" )\"\n478:                 if ( [ \"${query_response_lower}\" = \"true\" ] || [ \"${query_response_lower}\" = \"false\" ] ); then\n479:                     query_response=\"${query_response_lower}\"\n480:                     break\n481:                 fi\n482:                 printf \"please enter either '$( cf_color default_bright \"true\" )' or '$( cf_color default_bright \"false\" )':  \" query_response\n483:                 read query_response\n484:                 [ \"X${query_response}\" = \"X\" ] && query_response=\"${default}\"\n485:             done\n486:             value=\"${query_response}\"\n487: \n488:             # strip \" and ' on both sides\n489:             value=${value%\\\"}\n490:             value=${value%\\'}\n491:             value=${value#\\\"}\n492:             value=${value#\\'}\n493:         fi\n494: \n495:         export_and_save \"${varname}\" \"${value}\"\n496:     }\n497: \n498:     # prepare the tmp env file\n499:     if ! ${setup_is_default}; then\n500:         rm -f \"${env_file_tmp}\"\n501:         mkdir -p \"$( dirname \"${env_file_tmp}\" )\"\n502: \n503:         echo -e \"Start querying variables for setup '$( cf_color magenta ${setup_name} )', press enter to accept default values\\n\"\n504:     fi\n505: \n506:     # query for variables\n507:     cf_setup_interactive_body || return \"$?\"\n508: \n509:     # move the env file to the correct location for later use\n510:     if ! ${setup_is_default}; then\n511:         mv \"${env_file_tmp}\" \"${env_file}\"\n512:         echo -e \"\\nvariables written to ${env_file}\"\n513:     fi\n514: }\n515: \n516: cf_setup_software_stack() {\n517:     # Sets up the columnflow software stack as a base environment using conda (actually using the\n518:     # free and faster micromamba interface), lightweight virtual environments on top and git\n519:     # submodule initialization / updates.\n520:     #\n521:     # Arguments:\n522:     #   1. setup_name\n523:     #       The name of the setup.\n524:     #\n525:     # Required environment variables:\n526:     #   CF_BASE\n527:     #       The columnflow base directory.\n528:     #   CF_CONDA_BASE\n529:     #       The directory where conda / micromamba and conda envs will be installed.\n530:     #   CF_VENV_BASE\n531:     #       The base directory were virtual envs are installed.\n532:     #\n533:     # Optional environments variables:\n534:     #   CF_PYTHON_VERSION\n535:     #       The python version for the conda and venv installations. Defaults to \"3.9\".\n536:     #   CF_REMOTE_ENV\n537:     #       When true-ish, the software stack is sourced but not built.\n538:     #   CF_LOCAL_ENV\n539:     #       When not true-ish, the context is not meant for local development and only the \"cf_dev\" venv is built.\n540:     #       CF_INTERACTIVE_VENV_FILE is ignored in this case.\n541:     #   CF_INTERACTIVE_VENV_FILE\n542:     #       IF CF_LOCAL_ENV is true-ish, the venv setup of this file is sourced to start the interactive shell. When\n543:     #       empty, defaults to ${CF_BASE}/sandboxes/cf_dev.sh.\n544:     #   CF_REINSTALL_SOFTWARE\n545:     #       When true-ish, any existing software stack is removed and freshly installed.\n546:     #   CF_CONDA_ARCH\n547:     #       The OS / architecture for the conda installation. Defaults to \"linux-64\". For more info:\n548:     #       https://mamba.readthedocs.io/en/latest/installation/micromamba-installation.html#linux-and-macos\n549: \n550:     # check global variables\n551:     if [ -z \"${CF_BASE}\" ]; then\n552:         >&2 echo \"CF_BASE not defined, stopping software setup\"\n553:         return \"1\"\n554:     fi\n555:     if [ -z \"${CF_CONDA_BASE}\" ]; then\n556:         >&2 echo \"CF_CONDA_BASE not defined, stopping software setup\"\n557:         return \"2\"\n558:     fi\n559:     if [ -z \"${CF_VENV_BASE}\" ]; then\n560:         >&2 echo \"CF_VENV_BASE not defined, stopping software setup\"\n561:         return \"3\"\n562:     fi\n563: \n564:     # local variables\n565:     local shell_is_zsh=\"$( [ -z \"${ZSH_VERSION}\" ] && echo \"false\" || echo \"true\" )\"\n566:     local setup_name=\"${1}\"\n567:     local setup_is_default=\"false\"\n568:     [ \"${setup_name}\" = \"default\" ] && setup_is_default=\"true\"\n569:     local conda_arch=\"${CF_CONDA_ARCH:-linux-64}\"\n570:     local ret\n571: \n572:     # zsh options\n573:     if ${shell_is_zsh}; then\n574:         emulate -L bash\n575:         setopt globdots\n576:     fi\n577: \n578:     # default python version\n579:     export CF_PYTHON_VERSION=\"${CF_PYTHON_VERSION:-3.9}\"\n580: \n581:     # empty the PYTHONPATH, except for specific customizable paths\n582:     export PYTHONPATH=\"${CF_INITIAL_PYTHONPATH:-}\"\n583: \n584:     # persistent PATH and PYTHONPATH parts that should be\n585:     # priotized over any additions made in sandboxes\n586:     export CF_PERSISTENT_PATH=\"${CF_BASE}/bin:${CF_BASE}/modules/law/bin\"\n587:     export CF_PERSISTENT_PYTHONPATH=\"${CF_BASE}:${CF_BASE}/bin:${CF_BASE}/modules/law:${CF_BASE}/modules/order\"\n588: \n589:     # flavor specific paths\n590:     if [ ! -z \"${CF_FLAVOR}\" ]; then\n591:         [ -d \"${CF_BASE}/bin/${CF_FLAVOR}\" ] && export CF_PERSISTENT_PATH=\"${CF_PERSISTENT_PATH}:${CF_BASE}/bin/${CF_FLAVOR}\"\n592:     fi\n593: \n594:     # prepend them\n595:     export PATH=\"${CF_PERSISTENT_PATH}:${PATH}\"\n596:     export PYTHONPATH=\"${CF_PERSISTENT_PYTHONPATH}:${PYTHONPATH}\"\n597: \n598:     # also add the python path of the venv to be installed to propagate changes to any outer venv\n599:     export CF_CONDA_PYTHONPATH=\"${CF_CONDA_BASE}/lib/python${CF_PYTHON_VERSION}/site-packages\"\n600:     export PYTHONPATH=\"${PYTHONPATH}:${CF_CONDA_PYTHONPATH}\"\n601: \n602:     # update paths and flags\n603:     export MAMBA_ROOT_PREFIX=\"${CF_CONDA_BASE}\"\n604:     export MAMBA_EXE=\"${MAMBA_ROOT_PREFIX}/bin/micromamba\"\n605:     export PYTHONWARNINGS=\"${PYTHONWARNINGS:-ignore}\"\n606:     export PYTHONNOUSERSITE=\"${PYTHONNOUSERSITE:-1}\"\n607:     export GLOBUS_THREAD_MODEL=\"${GLOBUS_THREAD_MODEL:-none}\"\n608:     export VIRTUAL_ENV_DISABLE_PROMPT=\"${VIRTUAL_ENV_DISABLE_PROMPT:-1}\"\n609:     export MYPROXY_SERVER=\"${MYPROXY_SERVER:-myproxy.cern.ch}\"\n610:     export X509_CERT_DIR=\"${X509_CERT_DIR:-/cvmfs/grid.cern.ch/etc/grid-security/certificates}\"\n611:     export X509_VOMS_DIR=\"${X509_VOMS_DIR:-/cvmfs/grid.cern.ch/etc/grid-security/vomsdir}\"\n612:     export X509_VOMSES=\"${X509_VOMSES:-/cvmfs/grid.cern.ch/etc/grid-security/vomses}\"\n613:     export VOMS_USERCONF=\"${VOMS_USERCONF:-${X509_VOMSES}}\"\n614:     ulimit -s unlimited\n615: \n616:     #\n617:     # setup in local envs (not remote)\n618:     #\n619: \n620:     if ! ${CF_REMOTE_ENV}; then\n621:         # remote directories first if requested\n622:         if ${CF_REINSTALL_SOFTWARE}; then\n623:             echo \"removing conda setup at $( cf_color magenta ${CF_CONDA_BASE})\"\n624:             rm -rf \"${CF_CONDA_BASE}\"\n625: \n626:             echo \"removing software virtual envs at $( cf_color magenta ${CF_VENV_BASE})\"\n627:             rm -rf \"${CF_VENV_BASE}\"\n628:         fi\n629: \n630:         #\n631:         # conda / micromamba setup\n632:         #\n633: \n634:         # only needed in local envs\n635:         if ${CF_LOCAL_ENV}; then\n636:             # base environment\n637:             local conda_missing=\"$( [ -d \"${CF_CONDA_BASE}\" ] && echo \"false\" || echo \"true\" )\"\n638:             if ${conda_missing}; then\n639:                 echo\n640:                 cf_color magenta \"installing conda with micromamba interface at ${CF_CONDA_BASE}\"\n641: \n642:                 mkdir -p \"${CF_CONDA_BASE}/etc/profile.d\"\n643:                 curl -Ls \"https://micro.mamba.pm/api/micromamba/${conda_arch}/latest\" | tar -xvj -C \"${CF_CONDA_BASE}\" \"bin/micromamba\" > /dev/null\n644:                 2>&1 \"${CF_CONDA_BASE}/bin/micromamba\" shell hook -y --root-prefix \"$PWD\" &> micromamba.sh\n645:                 ret=\"$?\"\n646:                 if [ \"${ret}\" != \"0\" ]; then\n647:                     [ -f \"micromamba.sh\" ] && >&2 cat micromamba.sh\n648:                     return \"${ret}\"\n649:                 fi\n650:                 # make the setup file relocatable\n651:                 sed -i -r \"s|${CF_CONDA_BASE}|\\$\\{MAMBA_ROOT_PREFIX\\}|\" \"micromamba.sh\" || return \"$?\"\n652:                 mv \"micromamba.sh\" \"${CF_CONDA_BASE}/etc/profile.d/micromamba.sh\"\n653:                 cat << EOF > \"${CF_CONDA_BASE}/.mambarc\"\n654: changeps1: false\n655: always_yes: true\n656: channels:\n657:   - conda-forge\n658: EOF\n659:             fi\n660: \n661:             # initialize micromamba\n662:             source \"${CF_CONDA_BASE}/etc/profile.d/micromamba.sh\" \"\" || return \"$?\"\n663:             micromamba activate || return \"$?\"\n664:             echo \"initialized conda with $( cf_color magenta \"micromamba\" ) interface and $( cf_color magenta \"python ${CF_PYTHON_VERSION}\" )\"\n665: \n666:             # install packages\n667:             if ${conda_missing}; then\n668:                 echo\n669:                 cf_color cyan \"setting up conda / micromamba environment\"\n670:                 micromamba install \\\n671:                     gcc \\\n672:                     libgcc \\\n673:                     bash \\\n674:                     zsh \\\n675:                     \"python=${CF_PYTHON_VERSION}\" \\\n676:                     git \\\n677:                     git-lfs \\\n678:                     gfal2 \\\n679:                     gfal2-util \\\n680:                     python-gfal2 \\\n681:                     myproxy \\\n682:                     conda-pack \\\n683:                     || return \"$?\"\n684:                 micromamba clean --yes --all\n685: \n686:                 # add a file to conda/activate.d that handles the gfal setup transparently with conda-pack\n687:                 cat << EOF > \"${CF_CONDA_BASE}/etc/conda/activate.d/gfal_activate.sh\"\n688: export GFAL_CONFIG_DIR=\"\\${CONDA_PREFIX}/etc/gfal2.d\"\n689: export GFAL_PLUGIN_DIR=\"\\${CONDA_PREFIX}/lib/gfal2-plugins\"\n690: export X509_CERT_DIR=\"${X509_CERT_DIR}\"\n691: export X509_VOMS_DIR=\"${X509_VOMS_DIR}\"\n692: export X509_VOMSES=\"${X509_VOMSES}\"\n693: export VOMS_USERCONF=\"${VOMS_USERCONF}\"\n694: EOF\n695:                 echo\n696:             fi\n697:         fi\n698: \n699:         #\n700:         # venv setup\n701:         #\n702: \n703:         # - \"cf\"     : contains the minimal stack to run tasks and is sent alongside jobs\n704:         # - \"cf_dev\" : \"cf\" + additional python tools for local development (e.g. ipython)\n705:         # - custom   : when CF_INTERACTIVE_VENV_FILE is set, source the venv setup from there\n706: \n707:         source_venv() {\n708:             # all parameters must be given\n709:             local venv_file=\"$1\"\n710:             local venv_name=\"$2\"\n711:             # must be true or false\n712:             local use_subshell=\"$3\"\n713: \n714:             # source the file and catch the return code\n715:             local ret=\"0\"\n716:             if ${use_subshell}; then\n717:                 ( source \"${venv_file}\" \"\" \"silent\" )\n718:                 ret=\"$?\"\n719:             else\n720:                 source \"${venv_file}\" \"\" \"silent\"\n721:                 ret=\"$?\"\n722:             fi\n723: \n724:             # code 21 means \"version outdated\", all others are as usual\n725:             if [ \"${ret}\" = \"21\" ]; then\n726:                 >&2 echo\n727:                 >&2 echo \"WARNING: your venv '${venv_name}' is not up to date, please consider updating it in a new shell with\"\n728:                 >&2 echo \"WARNING: > CF_REINSTALL_SOFTWARE=1 source setup.sh $( ${setup_is_default} || echo \"${setup_name}\" )\"\n729:                 >&2 echo\n730:             elif [ \"${ret}\" != \"0\" ]; then\n731:                 return \"${ret}\"\n732:             fi\n733: \n734:             return \"0\"\n735:         }\n736: \n737:         # build the production sandbox in a subshell, only in local envs\n738:         if ${CF_LOCAL_ENV}; then\n739:             source_venv \"${CF_BASE}/sandboxes/cf.sh\" \"cf\" true || return \"$?\"\n740:         fi\n741: \n742:         # check if a custom interactive venv should be used, check the file, but only in local envs\n743:         local use_custom_interactive_venv=\"false\"\n744:         if ${CF_LOCAL_ENV} && [ ! -z \"${CF_INTERACTIVE_VENV_FILE}\" ]; then\n745:             # check existence\n746:             if [ ! -f \"${CF_INTERACTIVE_VENV_FILE}\" ]; then\n747:                 >&2 echo \"the interactive venv setup file ${CF_INTERACTIVE_VENV_FILE} does not exist\"\n748:                 return \"2\"\n749:             fi\n750:             use_custom_interactive_venv=\"true\"\n751:         fi\n752: \n753:         # build the dev sandbox, using a subshell if a custom venv is given that should be sourced afterwards\n754:         source_venv \"${CF_BASE}/sandboxes/cf_dev.sh\" \"cf_dev\" \"${use_custom_interactive_venv}\" || return \"$?\"\n755: \n756:         # source the custom interactive venv setup file if given\n757:         if ${use_custom_interactive_venv}; then\n758:             echo \"activating custom interactive venv from $( cf_color magenta \"${CF_INTERACTIVE_VENV_FILE}\" )\"\n759:             source_venv \"${CF_INTERACTIVE_VENV_FILE}\" \"$( basename \"${CF_INTERACTIVE_VENV_FILE%.*}\" )\" false || return \"$?\"\n760:         fi\n761: \n762:         # initialze submodules\n763:         if [ -e \"${CF_BASE}/.git\" ]; then\n764:             local m\n765:             for m in $( ls -1q \"${CF_BASE}/modules\" ); do\n766:                 cf_init_submodule \"${CF_BASE}\" \"modules/${m}\"\n767:             done\n768:         fi\n769:     fi\n770: \n771:     #\n772:     # setup in remote jobs\n773:     #\n774: \n775:     if ${CF_REMOTE_ENV}; then\n776:         # initialize conda\n777:         source \"${CF_CONDA_BASE}/etc/profile.d/micromamba.sh\" \"\" || return \"$?\"\n778:         micromamba activate || return \"$?\"\n779:         echo \"initialized conda with $( cf_color magenta \"micromamba\" ) interface and $( cf_color magenta \"python ${CF_PYTHON_VERSION}\" )\"\n780: \n781:         # source the production sandbox\n782:         source \"${CF_BASE}/sandboxes/cf.sh\" \"\" \"no\"\n783:     fi\n784: }\n785: \n786: cf_setup_post_install() {\n787:     # Performs additional, central setup steps after variables are set and software is installed. These steps are meant\n788:     # to be common to all setups and that can be adjusted later on through updates of the columnflow module.\n789:     #\n790:     # Current steps:\n791:     #   - setup git hooks\n792:     #   - setup law\n793:     #   - check size of the target tmp dir\n794:     #\n795:     # Required environment variables:\n796:     #   CF_LOCAL_ENV\n797:     #       Should be true or false, indicating if the setup is run in a local environment.\n798:     #   CF_REPO_BASE\n799:     #       The base directory of the analysis repository, which is used to determine the law home and config file.\n800:     #\n801:     # Optional environment variables:\n802:     #   CF_SKIP_SETUP_GIT_HOOKS\n803:     #       When set to true, the setup of git hooks is skipped.\n804:     #   CF_SKIP_LAW_INDEX\n805:     #       When set to true, the initial indexing of law tasks is skipped.\n806:     #   CF_SKIP_CHECK_TMP_DIR\n807:     #       When set to true, the check of the size of the target tmp directory is skipped.\n808: \n809:     #\n810:     # git hooks\n811:     #\n812: \n813:     # only in local env\n814:     if ! ${CF_SKIP_SETUP_GIT_HOOKS} && ${CF_LOCAL_ENV}; then\n815:         cf_setup_git_hooks || return \"$?\"\n816:     fi\n817: \n818:     #\n819:     # law setup\n820:     #\n821: \n822:     if [ ! -z \"${CF_REPO_BASE}\" ]; then\n823:         export LAW_HOME=\"${LAW_HOME:-${CF_REPO_BASE}/.law}\"\n824:         export LAW_CONFIG_FILE=\"${LAW_CONFIG_FILE:-${CF_REPO_BASE}/law.cfg}\"\n825: \n826:         if ${CF_LOCAL_ENV} && which law &> /dev/null; then\n827:             # source law's bash completion scipt\n828:             source \"$( law completion )\" \"\"\n829: \n830:             # add completion to the claw command\n831:             complete -o bashdefault -o default -F _law_complete claw\n832: \n833:             # silently index\n834:             if ! ${CF_SKIP_LAW_INDEX}; then\n835:                 law index -q\n836:             fi\n837:         fi\n838:     fi\n839: \n840:     #\n841:     # check the tmp directory size\n842:     #\n843: \n844:     if ! ${CF_SKIP_CHECK_TMP_DIR} && ${CF_LOCAL_ENV} && which law &> /dev/null; then\n845:         cf_check_tmp_dir\n846:     fi\n847: \n848:     return \"0\"\n849: }\n850: \n851: cf_check_tmp_dir() {\n852:     # Computes the size of all user-owned files in the target tmp directory and issues a warning when the size exceeds\n853:     # certain thresholds. If a variable CF_SKIP_TMP_CHECK is set to true, the check is skipped.\n854: \n855:     # check if skipping\n856:     if [ ! -z \"${CF_SKIP_TMP_CHECK}\" ] && ${CF_SKIP_TMP_CHECK}; then\n857:         return \"0\"\n858:     fi\n859: \n860:     # determine the tmp directory\n861:     local tmp_dir=\"$( law config target.tmp_dir )\"\n862:     local ret=\"$?\"\n863:     if [ \"${ret}\" != \"0\" ]; then\n864:         >&2 cf_color \"red\" \"cf_check_tmp_dir: 'law config target.tmp_dir' failed with error code ${ret}\"\n865:         return \"${ret}\"\n866:     elif [ -z \"${tmp_dir}\" ]; then\n867:         >&2 cf_color \"red\" \"cf_check_tmp_dir: 'law config target.tmp_dir' must not be empty\"\n868:         return \"2\"\n869:     elif [ ! -d \"${tmp_dir}\" ]; then\n870:         # nothing to do\n871:         return \"0\"\n872:     fi\n873: \n874:     # compute the size, with a notification shown if it takes too long\n875:     ( sleep 5 && cf_color yellow \"computing the size of your files in ${tmp_dir} ...\" ) &\n876:     local msg_pid=\"$!\"\n877:     local tmp_size=\"$( find \"${tmp_dir}\" -maxdepth 1 -user \"$( id -u )\" -exec du -cb {} + | grep 'total$' | cut -d $'\\t' -f 1 | sort | head -n 1 )\"\n878:     kill \"${msg_pid}\" 2> /dev/null\n879:     wait \"${msg_pid}\" 2> /dev/null\n880: \n881:     # warn above 1GB with color changing when above 2GB\n882:     local thresh1=\"1073741824\"\n883:     local thresh2=\"2147483648\"\n884:     if [ \"${tmp_size}\" -gt \"${thresh1}\" ]; then\n885:         local hsize=\"$( python -c \"import law; print(law.util.human_bytes(${tmp_size}, fmt=True))\" )\"\n886:         local color=\"$( [ \"${tmp_size}\" -lt \"${thresh2}\" ] && echo \"yellow\" || echo \"red\" )\"\n887:         echo\n888:         cf_color \"${color}\" \"the combined size of your files in the directory ${tmp_dir} is $( cf_color \"${color}_bright\" \"${hsize}\" )\"\n889:         cf_color \"${color}\" \"please consider cleaning up using $( cf_color \"${color}_bright\" \"'cf_remove_tmp [all]'\" )\"\n890:         echo\n891:     fi\n892: \n893:     return \"0\"\n894: }\n895: \n896: cf_setup_git_hooks() {\n897:     # Initializes lfs and custom githooks in the local checkout for both the columnflow\n898:     # (sub)repository, as well as the analysis repository in case a directory bin/githooks is found.\n899:     #\n900:     # Required environments variables:\n901:     #   CF_REMOTE_ENV (bool)\n902:     #       When true, no hooks are setup.\n903:     #   CF_CI_ENV (bool)\n904:     #       When true, no hooks are setup.\n905: \n906:     # do nothing when not local\n907:     if ${CF_REMOTE_ENV} || ${CF_CI_ENV}; then\n908:         return \"0\"\n909:     fi\n910: \n911:     # helper to setup hooks\n912:     setup_hooks() {\n913:         local repo_dir=\"$1\"\n914:         local src_dir=\"$2\"\n915:         local f\n916: \n917:         # determine the target hooks directory\n918:         local dst_dir=\"$( cd \"${repo_dir}\" && echo \"$( git rev-parse --git-dir )/hooks\" )\"\n919:         if [ \"$?\" != \"0\" ] || [ ! -d \"${dst_dir}\" ]; then\n920:             >&2 echo \"no git hooks directory found, cannot setup hooks\"\n921:             return \"30\"\n922:         fi\n923: \n924:         # remove existing hooks if requested\n925:         local flag_file=\"${dst_dir}/.cf_hooks_setup\"\n926:         if ${CF_REINSTALL_HOOKS}; then\n927:             # remove hooks\n928:             for f in $( ls -1 \"${dst_dir}\" ); do\n929:                 [ -f \"${dst_dir}/${f}\" ] && [[ \"${f}\" != *.sample ]] && rm -f \"${dst_dir}/${f}\"\n930:             done\n931:             # remove the flag file\n932:             rm -f \"${flag_file}\"\n933:         fi\n934: \n935:         # do nothing if hooks are already setup up\n936:         [ -f \"${flag_file}\" ] && return \"0\"\n937: \n938:         # detect if lfs hooks are already installed, as identified by the pre-push\n939:         local lfs_installed=\"false\"\n940:         for f in $( ls -1 \"${dst_dir}\"/{pre-push,pre-push-*} 2> /dev/null || true ); do\n941:             if [ -f \"${f}\" ] && [ ! -z \"$( cat \"${f}\" | grep \"git lfs pre-push\" )\" ]; then\n942:                 lfs_installed=\"true\"\n943:                 break\n944:             fi\n945:         done\n946: \n947:         # setup lfs if not done yet\n948:         if ! ${lfs_installed}; then\n949:             ( cd \"${repo_dir}\" && git lfs install > /dev/null ) || return \"$?\"\n950:         fi\n951: \n952:         # move all existing hooks and replace them with combined scripts\n953:         for f in $( ls -1 \"${dst_dir}\" ); do\n954:             # skip samples and directories\n955:             ( [ ! -f \"${dst_dir}/${f}\" ] || [[ \"${f}\" == *.sample ]] ) && continue\n956:             # move the file and create the new one\n957:             mv \"${dst_dir}/${f}\" \"${dst_dir}/${f}$( hook_postfix \"${dst_dir}\" \"${f}\" )\"\n958:             cp \"${CF_BASE}/bin/githooks/combined_hook.sh\" \"${dst_dir}/${f}\"\n959:         done\n960: \n961:         # setup all hooks in bin/githooks\n962:         for f in $( ls -1 \"${src_dir}\" ); do\n963:             # skip scripts and directories\n964:             ( [ ! -f \"${src_dir}/${f}\" ] || [[ \"${f}\" == *.sh ]] ) && continue\n965:             # link files\n966:             ln -s \"${src_dir}/${f}\" \"${dst_dir}/${f}$( hook_postfix \"${dst_dir}\" \"${f}\" )\"\n967:         done\n968: \n969:         # create the flag file\n970:         touch \"${flag_file}\"\n971: \n972:         return \"0\"\n973:     }\n974: \n975:     # helper to find a hook postfix number\n976:     hook_postfix() {\n977:         local dst_dir=\"$1\"\n978:         local hook_name=\"$2\"\n979: \n980:         for i in {1..100}; do\n981:             if [ ! -f \"${dst_dir}/${hook_name}-${i}\" ]; then\n982:                 echo \"-${i}\"\n983:                 return \"0\"\n984:             fi\n985:         done\n986: \n987:         >&2 echo \"could not determine hook postfix for ${hook_name} in ${dst_dir}\"\n988:         return \"31\"\n989:     }\n990: \n991:     # setup columnflow hooks\n992:     setup_hooks \"${CF_BASE}\" \"${CF_BASE}/bin/githooks\"\n993: \n994:     # setup repository hooks\n995:     if [ ! -z \"${CF_REPO_BASE}\" ] && [ -d \"${CF_REPO_BASE}/bin/githooks\" ]; then\n996:         setup_hooks \"${CF_REPO_BASE}\" \"${CF_REPO_BASE}/bin/githooks\"\n997:     fi\n998: \n999:     return \"0\"\n1000: }\n1001: [ ! -z \"${BASH_VERSION}\" ] && export -f cf_setup_git_hooks\n1002: \n1003: cf_init_submodule() {\n1004:     # Initializes and updates a git submodule.\n1005:     #\n1006:     # Arguments:\n1007:     #   1. base_path\n1008:     #     The path of the base directory relative to which the module_path is evaluated.\n1009:     #   2. submodule_path\n1010:     #       The path to the submodule, relative to base_path.\n1011: \n1012:     # local variables\n1013:     local base_path=\"${1}\"\n1014:     local submodule_path=\"${2}\"\n1015: \n1016:     # do nothing in remote jobs\n1017:     ${CF_REMOTE_ENV} && return \"0\"\n1018: \n1019:     # do nothing when the path does not exist or it is not a submodule\n1020:     if [ ! -e \"${base_path}/${submodule_path}\" ]; then\n1021:         return \"0\"\n1022:     fi\n1023: \n1024:     # initialize the submodule when the directory is empty\n1025:     if [ \"$( ls -1q \"${base_path}/${submodule_path}\" | wc -l )\" = \"0\" ]; then\n1026:         ( cd \"${base_path}\" && git submodule update --init --recursive \"${submodule_path}\" )\n1027:     else\n1028:         # update when not on a working branch and there are no changes\n1029:         local detached_head=\"$( ( cd \"${base_path}/${submodule_path}\"; git symbolic-ref -q HEAD &> /dev/null ) && echo \"true\" || echo \"false\" )\"\n1030:         local changed_files=\"$( cd \"${base_path}/${submodule_path}\"; git status --porcelain=v1 2> /dev/null | wc -l )\"\n1031:         if ! ${detached_head} && [ \"${changed_files}\" = \"0\" ]; then\n1032:             ( cd \"${base_path}\" && git submodule update --init --recursive \"${submodule_path}\" )\n1033:         fi\n1034:     fi\n1035: }\n1036: [ ! -z \"${BASH_VERSION}\" ] && export -f cf_init_submodule\n1037: \n1038: cf_cast_bool() {\n1039:     # lower case\n1040:     local value=\"$( cf_lower_case \"$1\" )\"\n1041:     if [ \"${value}\" = \"1\" ] || [ \"${value}\" = \"yes\" ] || [ \"${value}\" = \"true\" ]; then\n1042:         echo \"true\"\n1043:     else\n1044:         echo \"false\"\n1045:     fi\n1046: }\n1047: [ ! -z \"${BASH_VERSION}\" ] && export -f cf_cast_bool\n1048: \n1049: cf_export_bool() {\n1050:     local shell_is_zsh=\"$( [ -z \"${ZSH_VERSION}\" ] && echo \"false\" || echo \"true\" )\"\n1051:     local name=\"$1\"\n1052:     if ${shell_is_zsh}; then\n1053:         export \"${name}\"=\"$( cf_cast_bool \"${(P)name}\" )\"\n1054:     else\n1055:         export \"${name}\"=\"$( cf_cast_bool \"${!name}\" )\"\n1056:     fi\n1057: }\n1058: [ ! -z \"${BASH_VERSION}\" ] && export -f cf_export_bool\n1059: \n1060: cf_color() {\n1061:     # get arguments\n1062:     local color=\"$1\"\n1063:     local msg=\"${@:2}\"\n1064: \n1065:     # just echo the message as is in certain conditions\n1066:     if ${CF_REMOTE_ENV} || ${CF_RTD_ENV} || ${CF_CI_ENV}; then\n1067:         echo \"${msg}\"\n1068:         return \"0\"\n1069:     fi\n1070: \n1071:     # zsh options\n1072:     local shell_is_zsh=\"$( [ -z \"${ZSH_VERSION}\" ] && echo \"false\" || echo \"true\" )\"\n1073:     if ${shell_is_zsh}; then\n1074:         emulate -L bash\n1075:         setopt globdots\n1076:     fi\n1077: \n1078:     case \"${color}\" in\n1079:         default)\n1080:             echo -e \"\\x1b[0;49;39m${msg}\\x1b[0m\"\n1081:             ;;\n1082:         red)\n1083:             echo -e \"\\x1b[0;49;31m${msg}\\x1b[0m\"\n1084:             ;;\n1085:         green)\n1086:             echo -e \"\\x1b[0;49;32m${msg}\\x1b[0m\"\n1087:             ;;\n1088:         yellow)\n1089:             echo -e \"\\x1b[0;49;33m${msg}\\x1b[0m\"\n1090:             ;;\n1091:         blue)\n1092:             echo -e \"\\x1b[0;49;34m${msg}\\x1b[0m\"\n1093:             ;;\n1094:         magenta)\n1095:             echo -e \"\\x1b[0;49;35m${msg}\\x1b[0m\"\n1096:             ;;\n1097:         cyan)\n1098:             echo -e \"\\x1b[0;49;36m${msg}\\x1b[0m\"\n1099:             ;;\n1100:         default_bright)\n1101:             echo -e \"\\x1b[1;49;39m${msg}\\x1b[0m\"\n1102:             ;;\n1103:         red_bright)\n1104:             echo -e \"\\x1b[1;49;31m${msg}\\x1b[0m\"\n1105:             ;;\n1106:         green_bright)\n1107:             echo -e \"\\x1b[1;49;32m${msg}\\x1b[0m\"\n1108:             ;;\n1109:         yellow_bright)\n1110:             echo -e \"\\x1b[1;49;33m${msg}\\x1b[0m\"\n1111:             ;;\n1112:         blue_bright)\n1113:             echo -e \"\\x1b[1;49;34m${msg}\\x1b[0m\"\n1114:             ;;\n1115:         magenta_bright)\n1116:             echo -e \"\\x1b[1;49;35m${msg}\\x1b[0m\"\n1117:             ;;\n1118:         cyan_bright)\n1119:             echo -e \"\\x1b[1;49;36m${msg}\\x1b[0m\"\n1120:             ;;\n1121:         *)\n1122:             echo \"${msg}\"\n1123:             ;;\n1124:     esac\n1125: }\n1126: [ ! -z \"${BASH_VERSION}\" ] && export -f cf_color\n1127: \n1128: cf_lower_case() {\n1129:     # cross-shell lower case helper\n1130:     echo \"$1\" | tr \"[:upper:]\" \"[:lower:]\"\n1131: }\n1132: \n1133: cf_upper_case() {\n1134:     # cross-shell upper case helper\n1135:     echo \"$1\" | tr \"[:lower:]\" \"[:upper:]\"\n1136: }\n1137: \n1138: main() {\n1139:     # Invokes the main action of this script, catches possible error codes and prints a message.\n1140: \n1141:     # run the actual setup\n1142:     if setup_columnflow \"$@\"; then\n1143:         cf_color green \"columnflow successfully setup\"\n1144:         return \"0\"\n1145:     else\n1146:         local code=\"$?\"\n1147:         cf_color red \"columnflow setup failed with code ${code}\"\n1148:         return \"${code}\"\n1149:     fi\n1150: }\n1151: \n1152: # always cast expected boolean values\n1153: for flag_name in \\\n1154:         CF_SETUP \\\n1155:         CF_SKIP_SETUP \\\n1156:         CF_REMOTE_ENV \\\n1157:         CF_REINSTALL_SOFTWARE \\\n1158:         CF_REINSTALL_HOOKS \\\n1159:         CF_SKIP_BANNER \\\n1160:         CF_SKIP_SETUP_GIT_HOOKS \\\n1161:         CF_SKIP_LAW_INDEX \\\n1162:         CF_SKIP_CHECK_TMP_DIR \\\n1163:         CF_ON_HTCONDOR \\\n1164:         CF_ON_SLURM \\\n1165:         CF_ON_GRID \\\n1166:         CF_RTD_ENV \\\n1167:         CF_CI_ENV \\\n1168:         CF_DEV \\\n1169:         ; do\n1170:     cf_export_bool \"${flag_name}\"\n1171: done\n1172: \n1173: # entry point\n1174: if ! ${CF_SKIP_SETUP}; then\n1175:     main \"$@\"\n1176: fi\n\n(End of file - total 1176 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\n\nsetup_columnflow() {\n    # Runs the entire project setup, leading to a collection of environment variables starting with\n    # \"CF_\", the installation of the software stack via virtual environments, and optionally an\n    # interactive setup where the user can configure certain variables.\n    #\n    # Arguments:\n    #   1. The name of the setup. \"default\" (which is itself the default when no name is set)\n    #      triggers a setup with good defaults, avoiding all queries to the user and the writing of\n    #      a custom setup file. See \"interactive_setup()\" for more info.\n    #\n    # Boolean flags are considered true-ish if they are \"1\", \"yes\" or \"true\" (case-insensitive).\n    #\n    # Optionally preconfigured environment variables:\n    #   CF_REINSTALL_SOFTWARE\n    #       When true-ish, any existing software stack is removed and freshly installed.\n    #   CF_REINSTALL_HOOKS\n    #       When true-ish, existing git hooks are removed and linked again.\n    #   CF_REMOTE_ENV","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"setup.sh","time":{"start":1776113429818,"end":1776113429828}}}]}
