{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_27763f7d3ffeGH5F5fsk7eU9xK","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d889c4cd9001dKLZ2ZKnohdOjK","parts":[{"id":"prt_d889c58cb001rHX576KxkDaYnV","messageID":"msg_d889c4cd9001dKLZ2ZKnohdOjK","sessionID":"ses_27763f7d3ffeGH5F5fsk7eU9xK","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3eae48c76526402a84f76b7e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/sandboxes/_setup_venv.sh","limit":100},"output":"<path>/workspace/sandboxes/_setup_venv.sh</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: #!/usr/bin/env bash\n2: \n3: # Script that installs and sources a virtual environment. Distinctions are made depending on whether\n4: # the venv is already present, and whether the script is called as part of a remote (law) job\n5: # (CF_REMOTE_ENV=true).\n6: #\n7: # Four environment variables are expected to be set before this script is called:\n8: #   CF_SANDBOX_FILE\n9: #       The path of the file that contained the sandbox definition and that sourced _this_ script.\n10: #       It is used to derive a hash for defining the installation directory and to set the value of\n11: #       the LAW_SANDBOX variable.\n12: #   CF_VENV_BASE\n13: #       The base directory where virtual environments will be installed. Set by the main setup.sh.\n14: #   CF_VENV_NAME\n15: #       The name of the virtual environment. It will be installed into $CF_VENV_BASE/$CF_VENV_NAME.\n16: #   CF_VENV_REQUIREMENTS\n17: #       The requirements file containing packages that are installed on top of\n18: #       $CF_BASE/sandboxes/cf.txt.\n19: #\n20: # Upon venv activation, two environment variables are set in addition to those exported by the venv:\n21: #   CF_DEV\n22: #       Set to \"1\" when CF_VENV_NAME ends with \"_dev\", and \"0\" otherwise.\n23: #   LAW_SANDBOX\n24: #       Set to the name of the sandbox to be correctly interpreted later on by law. See\n25: #       CF_SANDBOX_FILE above.\n26: #\n27: # Optional arguments:\n28: #   1. mode\n29: #      The setup mode. Different values are accepted:\n30: #        - ''/install: The virtual environment is installed when not existing yet and sourced.\n31: #        - reinstall:  The virtual environment is removed first, then reinstalled and sourced.\n32: #        - update:     The virtual environment is removed first in case it is outdated, then\n33: #                      reinstalled and sourced.\n34: #      Please note that if the mode is empty ('') and the environment variable CF_SANDBOX_SETUP_MODE\n35: #      is defined, its value is used instead.\n36: #\n37: #   2. versioncheck\n38: #      When \"yes\", perform a version check, print a warning in case of a mismatch and set a specific\n39: #      exit code (21). When \"no\", the check is skipped alltogether. When \"silent\", no warning is\n40: #      printed but an exit code might be set. When \"warn\" (the default), a warning might be printed,\n41: #      but the exit code remains unchanged.\n42: #\n43: # Note on remote jobs:\n44: # When the CF_REMOTE_ENV variable is set (usually set by a remote job bootstrap script) and\n45: # true-ish, no mode is supported and an error is printed when it is set to a non-empty value. In any\n46: # case, no installation will happen but the setup is reused from a pre-compiled software bundle that\n47: # is fetched from a local or remote location and unpacked.\n48: \n49: setup_venv() {\n50:     local shell_is_zsh=\"$( [ -z \"${ZSH_VERSION}\" ] && echo \"false\" || echo \"true\" )\"\n51:     local this_file=\"$( ${shell_is_zsh} && echo \"${(%):-%x}\" || echo \"${BASH_SOURCE[0]}\" )\"\n52:     local this_dir=\"$( cd \"$( dirname \"${this_file}\" )\" && pwd )\"\n53:     local orig_dir=\"${PWD}\"\n54: \n55:     # zsh options\n56:     if ${shell_is_zsh}; then\n57:         emulate -L bash\n58:         setopt globdots\n59:     fi\n60: \n61:     # source the main setup script to access helpers\n62:     CF_SKIP_SETUP=\"true\" source \"${this_dir}/../setup.sh\" \"\" || return \"$?\"\n63: \n64: \n65:     #\n66:     # get and check arguments\n67:     #\n68: \n69:     local mode=\"${1:-}\"\n70:     local versioncheck=\"${2:-warn}\"\n71: \n72:     # default mode\n73:     if [ -z \"${mode}\" ]; then\n74:         if [ ! -z \"${CF_SANDBOX_SETUP_MODE}\" ]; then\n75:             mode=\"${CF_SANDBOX_SETUP_MODE}\"\n76:         else\n77:             mode=\"install\"\n78:         fi\n79:     fi\n80: \n81:     # value checks\n82:     if [ \"${mode}\" != \"install\" ] && [ \"${mode}\" != \"reinstall\" ] && [ \"${mode}\" != \"update\" ]; then\n83:         >&2 echo \"unknown venv setup mode '${mode}'\"\n84:         return \"1\"\n85:     fi\n86:     if ${CF_REMOTE_ENV} && [ \"${mode}\" != \"install\" ]; then\n87:         >&2 echo \"the venv setup mode must be 'install' or empty in remote jobs, but got '${mode}'\"\n88:         return \"2\"\n89:     fi\n90:     if [ \"${versioncheck}\" != \"yes\" ] && [ \"${versioncheck}\" != \"no\" ] && [ \"${versioncheck}\" != \"silent\" ] && [ \"${versioncheck}\" != \"warn\" ]; then\n91:         >&2 echo \"unknown versioncheck setting '${versioncheck}'\"\n92:         return \"3\"\n93:     fi\n94: \n95: \n96:     #\n97:     # check required global variables\n98:     #\n99: \n100:     local sandbox_file=\"${CF_SANDBOX_FILE}\"\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 370. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\n\n# Script that installs and sources a virtual environment. Distinctions are made depending on whether\n# the venv is already present, and whether the script is called as part of a remote (law) job\n# (CF_REMOTE_ENV=true).\n#\n# Four environment variables are expected to be set before this script is called:\n#   CF_SANDBOX_FILE\n#       The path of the file that contained the sandbox definition and that sourced _this_ script.\n#       It is used to derive a hash for defining the installation directory and to set the value of\n#       the LAW_SANDBOX variable.\n#   CF_VENV_BASE\n#       The base directory where virtual environments will be installed. Set by the main setup.sh.\n#   CF_VENV_NAME\n#       The name of the virtual environment. It will be installed into $CF_VENV_BASE/$CF_VENV_NAME.\n#   CF_VENV_REQUIREMENTS\n#       The requirements file containing packages that are installed on top of\n#       $CF_BASE/sandboxes/cf.txt.\n#\n# Upon venv activation, two environment variables are set in addition to those exported by the venv:","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"sandboxes/_setup_venv.sh","time":{"start":1776113441788,"end":1776113441793}}}]}
